EntityName: Dualling an existing single carriageway - including accompanying structures & earthworks - Low Scenario
EntityDescription:
This asset represents median modelled carbon estimates, based on 10 carbon assessments, for dualling an existing single carriageway (including accompanying structures and earthworks). Values are normalised per kilometre of road. Median and high estimates are available in the equivalent assets.

Individual assessments are available to capture what percentage of the road is dualled through offline dualling (meaning that the existing single carriageway is maintained to carry one direction of traffic), as opposed to constructing two new carriageways. These include A1-A3 (construction materials) and A5 (construction plant). They represent an average topography, with standard materials and construction processes.

Please refer to the legal disclaimer in the attached assessment file for further information.
AssessmentName: Dualling an existing single carriageway - including accompanying structures & earthworks - 90% updated through offline dualling, 10% updated through constructing two new carriageways
EntityElementName: Superstructure (Int) (2.7 Internal Walls and Partitions; 2.8 Internal Doors)
CarbonNotes: The carbon equivalent values provided here are representative of a low estimate for dualling a single carriageway (including accompanying structures and earthworks) for 1km. This assumes that 90% of the route is updated through offline dualling (meaning that the existing single carriageway is maintained to carry one direction of traffic), with 10% of the route updated through constructing two new carriageways. Values are based on 10 assessments, normalised per km of carriageway, and only include A1-A3 (construction materials) and A5 (construction plant). They represent a standard design, an average topography, with standard materials and construction processes. Please refer to the legal disclaimer in the attached assessment file for further information.

This asset represents median modelled carbon estimates, based on 5 carbon assessments, for building a new grade-separated two-bridge roundabout (including earthworks). Low and high estimates are available in the equivalent assets.

Individual assessments are available to capture how the number of arms at the junction. These include A1-A3 (construction materials) and A5 (construction plant). They represent an average topography, with standard materials and construction processes.
